# .cursorignore
#
# Keeps Cursor's semantic indexer focused on framework source and docs.
# Hides: secrets, virtualenv noise, ephemeral runtime state, agent memory.
#
# Preserves full functionality: .cursorignore blocks the INDEXER, not file
# access. Cursor can still create, read, run, and modify any of these
# files when a task requires it (e.g. populating .venv for semantic
# memory, writing task JSON via queue-drainer.mjs, recording agent
# memory via memory-manager.mjs). This is noise control to sharpen
# Cursor's @-mentions and auto-context — not a capability restriction.

# ─── Secrets (gitignored too — belt + suspenders for on-disk scans) ──
.env
.env.local
.env.*.local
.paperclip.env

# ─── Python virtualenv (created on-demand when semantic memory installed) ──
# 3000+ package files would drown framework source in Cursor's index.
# Cursor can still run `python -m venv .venv` and populate it normally.
.venv/
venv/
__pycache__/
*.pyc

# ─── Node (zero deps in this repo; safe default if ever added) ────
node_modules/

# ─── Ephemeral runtime outputs (regenerated by framework scripts) ──
agents/model-intel.json
agents/pattern-hunt-output.json
pm/

# ─── Live task state (access via queue-drainer.mjs — don't cite stale JSON) ──
tasks/queue/
tasks/in-progress/

# ─── Agent memory files (access via memory-manager.mjs recall) ──
# Indexing would have Cursor cite fragmented agent thoughts as authoritative.
agents/*/memory/*.json
agents/*/memory/*.jsonl

# ─── Logs & build artifacts ─────────────────────────────────────
*.log
logs/
dist/
build/
coverage/

# ─── OS cruft ───────────────────────────────────────────────────
.DS_Store
Thumbs.db
.idea/
